00:19:29.461 --> 00:19:31.255
Hey. I don't wanna see that.

259
00:19:31.338 --> 00:19:33.465
Now. you get up on this bike.
and you try again. okay?

260
00:19:33.549 --> 00:19:35.676
And you've gotta follow my instructions.

261
00:19:37.302 --> 00:19:39.304
Hey. I need to talk to Mr. Slayton.

262
00:19:39.388 --> 00:19:40.806
So. we'll continue this tomorrow.

263
00:19:51.525 --> 00:19:52.526
Deke.

264
00:20:18.468 --> 00:20:20.387
I'm making a change in your crew.

265
00:20:21.722 --> 00:20:22.931
Gordo's out.

266
00:20:23.849 --> 00:20:25.058
Shit.

267
00:20:28.604 --> 00:20:30.814
-What'd he do now?
-It's not that.

268
00:20:31.690 --> 00:20:34.026
Your new LEM pilot
will be one of the new astronauts.

269
00:20:34.109 --> 00:20:35.652
One of the female astronauts.

270
00:20:38.030 --> 00:20:39.323
You're kidding me.

271
00:20:42.326 --> 00:20:44.328
You put him on 15. Deke.

272
00:20:46.121 --> 00:20:47.748
He's been up there with me twice before

273
00:20:47.831 --> 00:20:49.875
and training with me every day
for the past nine months.

274
00:20:49.958 --> 00:20:52.544
And he's the best goddamn LEM pilot
we have in the program.

275
00:20:52.628 --> 00:20:55.380
These women can fly.
You've seen what they're capable of.

276
00:20:55.464 --> 00:20:57.966
Come on. Deke. This is a publicity stunt.

277
00:20:58.717 --> 00:21:01.053
All due respect. Karen.
this is my decision.

278
00:21:01.136 --> 00:21:03.847
Well. then I understand it even less.
You're rushing into this.

279
00:21:03.931 --> 00:21:05.307
-You're gonna make a mistake.
-Karen.

280
00:21:08.268 --> 00:21:10.312
Look. they need more training.

281
00:21:11.897 --> 00:21:13.774
They're not ready. Deke. Not for 15.

282
00:21:13.857 --> 00:21:14.858
I disagree.

283
00:21:15.609 --> 00:21:17.528
They've all earned their place
in this program.

284
00:21:17.611 --> 00:21:19.738
And I say they're ready to fly.

285
00:21:19.821 --> 00:21:21.782
That's easy to say
when you're not going up there.

286
00:21:24.952 --> 00:21:26.870
You don't want the flight. say the words.

287
00:21:27.788 --> 00:21:30.040
You can get drunk
and watch it on TV with Gordo

288
00:21:30.123 --> 00:21:32.000
and bitch about how unfair the world is.

289
00:21:32.084 --> 00:21:33.335
You won't see me there.

290
00:21:36.338 --> 00:21:37.673
So. you want the flight or not?

291
00:21:41.051 --> 00:21:42.427
Yeah. I want the

292
00:21:43.345 --> 00:21:44.429
Good.

293
00:21:50.435 --> 00:21:53.188
Oh. shit. Should I go talk to her?

294
00:21:54.439 --> 00:21:56.650
Not if you wanna walk out of here alive.

295
00:21:58.819 --> 00:22:00.487
I'll break the news to Gordo.

296
00:22:00.988 --> 00:22:02.406
Already done.

297
00:22:02.781 --> 00:22:04.700
It was my call. My responsibility.

298
00:22:05.284 --> 00:22:07.703
-How'd he take it?
-About the same way she did.

299
00:22:09.371 --> 00:22:12.165
You should have dinner with your
new crewmate tonight. you and Sedge.

300
00:22:13.083 --> 00:22:16.795
Have a couple drinks. Break bread.
Get to know each other a little.

301
00:22:19.006 --> 00:22:20.215
Great.

302
00:22:21.925 --> 00:22:23.802
So. who's the lucky lady?

303
00:22:26.346 --> 00:22:30.017
You know.
a lot of eyes are gonna be on you now.

304
00:22:30.100 --> 00:22:31.977
A lot of expectations.

305
00:22:33.478 --> 00:22:35.314
You just gotta
put all that out of your mind.

306
00:22:35.397 --> 00:22:38.775
You just. you know. focus on the mission.
It's the only thing that matters.

307
00:22:38.859 --> 00:22:40.652
And. you know. remember.
it's not all on you.

308
00:22:40.736 --> 00:22:41.904
You know. we're a crew.

309
00:22:41.987 --> 00:22:43.906
That's right. We're 15.

310
00:22:45.032 --> 00:22:47.409
Just the three of us.
We rely on each other.

311
00:22:47.910 --> 00:22:50.078
-Damn right.
-Could you pass the A1. please?

312
00:22:53.248 --> 00:22:55.042
And it's gonna be
your first time in space.

313
00:22:55.876 --> 00:22:57.461
Everybody understands that.

314
00:23:00.380 --> 00:23:02.841
It's gonna be
your first time in space too. right?

315
00:23:02.925 --> 00:23:04.092
Uh-huh.

316
00:23:04.176 --> 00:23:06.470
Old Sedgey used to fly Phantoms in Nam.

317
00:23:06.553 --> 00:23:08.514
He's been flying jets
ever since the Air Force Academy.

318
00:23:08.597 --> 00:23:10.265
but we won't hold that against him.

319
00:23:10.349 --> 00:23:11.600
Go Falcons.

320
00:23:11.683 --> 00:23:13.352
You know.
you guys gotta try the baked potato.

321
00:23:13.810 --> 00:23:16.063
-It's outstanding.
-Fantastic.

322
00:23:16.146 --> 00:23:19.733
You know I guess
what I'm really trying to get to

323
00:23:19.816 --> 00:23:21.443
Yep. Please. get to it.

324
00:23:24.154 --> 00:23:25.447
I'm trying to get to it

325
00:23:25.531 --> 00:23:28.909
You know. between me and Sedgey. we've got
a lot of experience under our belts.

326
00:23:28.992 --> 00:23:32.037
So if you just follow our lead.

327
00:23:32.996 --> 00:23:35.040
you won't have anything to worry about.

328
00:23:36.959 --> 00:23:39.878
-I'm not worried.
-Good.

329
00:23:40.504 --> 00:23:42.965
I've actually been flying
longer than either of you.

330
00:23:43.674 --> 00:23:48.345
In fact. I was in Mercury 13
before you got into Gemini.

331
00:23:48.428 --> 00:23:50.013
So. in a sense.

332
00:23:50.597 --> 00:23:52.224
I have seniority here.

333
00:23:53.934 --> 00:23:54.935
Isn't that funny?

334
00:23:58.480 --> 00:23:59.940
Yeah. this is good.

335
00:24:49.573 --> 00:24:50.741
There you are.

336
00:24:53.368 --> 00:24:55.913
Where have you been?
Dinner's in half an hour.

337
00:24:55.996 --> 00:24:58.874
And Fred and Susie are probably
already on their way over.

338
00:25:00.626 --> 00:25:02.377
Sorry. Just...

339
00:25:03.086 --> 00:25:05.380
a couple things come up at the office.

340
00:25:09.551 --> 00:25:10.552
Are you...

341
00:25:16.558 --> 00:25:18.018
Jesus Christ.

342
00:25:19.895 --> 00:25:21.104
You're drunk.

343
00:25:22.523 --> 00:25:25.067
You're just not gonna
let me enjoy this. are you?

344
00:25:25.150 --> 00:25:28.695
I'm sorry. Trace. I just...

345
00:25:29.863 --> 00:25:31.114
What. Gordo?

346
00:25:32.074 --> 00:25:33.200
What?

347
00:25:39.373 --> 00:25:40.916
I'm off 15.

348
00:25:42.543 --> 00:25:44.378
Deke replaced me with Molly Cobb.

349
00:25:45.754 --> 00:25:47.130
She's taking my ride.

350
00:25:49.883 --> 00:25:51.176
Honey.

351
00:25:51.260 --> 00:25:53.220
So. she gets the moon.

352
00:25:54.471 --> 00:25:57.766
and I get... shit.

353
00:26:03.564 --> 00:26:04.857
I'm so sorry.

354
00:26:09.027 --> 00:26:11.613
Hey. you know what?
I'm gonna tell Sheila to go home

355
00:26:11.697 --> 00:26:13.448
-and you just
-Hey. no. No.

356
00:26:14.825 --> 00:26:19.329
No. No. we're celebrating you tonight.

357
00:26:19.413 --> 00:26:21.456
-Are you sure?
-Damn straight.

358
00:26:21.540 --> 00:26:24.209
Another Stevens is an astronaut.

359
00:26:24.293 --> 00:26:26.879
I mean. that demands a celebration.

360
00:26:26.962 --> 00:26:29.464
In fact. I'm gonna call Jim Rathmann.

361
00:26:30.048 --> 00:26:31.675
Next week. you and me will go down there.

362
00:26:31.758 --> 00:26:35.095
we're gonna pick out
a brand-new Vette for you.

363
00:26:37.431 --> 00:26:38.932
I can't go next week.

364
00:26:40.142 --> 00:26:41.435
Why not?

365
00:26:42.060 --> 00:26:43.896
They're sending me out to the Cape
to help prep.

366
00:26:47.691 --> 00:26:48.859
For how long?

367
00:26:49.568 --> 00:26:51.528
A week. Maybe a little longer.

368
00:26:51.612 --> 00:26:52.654
A week?

369
00:26:54.406 --> 00:26:55.782
I mean. well

370
00:26:57.284 --> 00:27:00.037
Shouldn't we. like.
talk through that stuff

371
00:27:00.120 --> 00:27:02.789
before you just agree
to run off and go to Florida?

372
00:27:04.291 --> 00:27:06.585
Well. that's not how this works. Gordo.
You know that.

373
00:27:08.837 --> 00:27:11.048
I go where I'm told. just like you.

374
00:27:38.200 --> 00:27:39.910
Hey. Molly's getting 15.

375
00:27:39.993 --> 00:27:41.286
She is.

376
00:27:41.370 --> 00:27:43.747
And I'm not exactly
supposed to tell you this.

377
00:27:43.830 --> 00:27:47.417
but word is you're gonna be her backup.

378
00:27:52.047 --> 00:27:53.757
She's the best pilot in our class.

379
00:27:53.841 --> 00:27:56.134
Plus. she thrives under pressure.

380
00:27:56.218 --> 00:27:57.886
Half the time
I think she tries to create it.

381
00:27:57.970 --> 00:28:02.057
Well. Baldwin doesn't put up
with any shit and Molly loves a shitstorm.

382
00:28:02.933 --> 00:28:05.310
which means you have a real shot
at getting bumped up.

383
00:28:05.811 --> 00:28:09.273
Just keep on doing what you do.
And keep your nose clean.

384
00:28:14.611 --> 00:28:18.031
Well. here's to the first American woman
on the moon.

385
00:28:18.115 --> 00:28:19.491
Whoever she may be.

386
00:28:24.621 --> 00:28:26.123
-I got the next round.
-Thank you.

387
00:28:28.000 --> 00:28:29.001
Please.

388
00:28:29.585 --> 00:28:32.754
So. when do you get off work?

389
00:28:34.339 --> 00:28:35.799
Not soon enough.

390
00:28:36.842 --> 00:28:38.135
-Can we have another round?
-Yeah.

391
00:28:40.137 --> 00:28:41.597
-Hi.
-Hello.

392
00:28:42.681 --> 00:28:44.016
-Bourbon for Yeah.
-Sure.

393
00:28:46.977 --> 00:28:48.854
You and lady astronaut over there

394
00:28:48.937 --> 00:28:51.565
have been spending
an awful lot of time together lately.

395
00:28:52.482 --> 00:28:54.234
Yeah. I'd make a move
while you still can. Lar.

396
00:28:55.068 --> 00:28:58.238
I mean. chick like that
won't be on the market long.

397
00:28:58.322 --> 00:29:03.327
And I bet that astronaut tail...
it's outta this world.

398
00:29:14.421 --> 00:29:16.673
And I was nice to her the whole time.

399
00:29:17.257 --> 00:29:19.760
Offered to help her out.
show her the ropes.

400
00:29:20.761 --> 00:29:23.388
And all she gave me was attitude. Like

401
00:29:24.264 --> 00:29:26.767
She acted like
she's already been up there before.

402
00:29:28.602 --> 00:29:29.686
What?

403
00:29:31.772 --> 00:29:32.814
I don't know.

404
00:29:34.441 --> 00:29:36.527
You know. I don't think she likes men.

405
00:29:37.277 --> 00:29:39.363
-You know what I mean?
-What? Hey. no.

406
00:29:39.446 --> 00:29:41.406
-You just brushed your teeth.
-It's like Listerine.

407
00:29:41.490 --> 00:29:44.076
-Okay. Yeah?
-Yeah.

408
00:29:44.660 --> 00:29:45.702
Great.

409
00:29:57.714 --> 00:30:00.384
He does not respect women.

410
00:30:01.176 --> 00:30:03.095
that's for damn sure.

411
00:30:10.435 --> 00:30:12.187
He probably thinks I'm a lesbian.

412
00:30:17.860 --> 00:30:20.028
I've often thought of myself as a lesbian.

413
00:30:22.281 --> 00:30:24.616
He was so goddamn patronizing.

414
00:30:27.160 --> 00:30:29.621
Telling me that I shouldn't worry

415
00:30:30.372 --> 00:30:33.876
because they would be there
to hold my hand.

416
00:30:36.336 --> 00:30:38.547
It sounds like
he doesn't know you very well.

417
00:30:39.173 --> 00:30:41.258
Yeah. well. why would he?

418
00:30:45.804 --> 00:30:50.142
I mean. we are invisible
to the "real astronauts."

419
00:30:54.521 --> 00:30:56.398
He thinks this program's a joke.

420
00:31:02.863 --> 00:31:05.782
It's just ridiculous.
I don't know why you agreed to it.

421
00:31:05.866 --> 00:31:08.410
It's not gonna help with everything
that happened with Patty.

422
00:31:08.493 --> 00:31:11.079
Look. it's not about that. okay?

423
00:31:13.832 --> 00:31:15.417
Deke's got final say on the crew.

424
00:31:15.959 --> 00:31:17.628
-Yeah. but
-You heard him. I'd be off 15.

425
00:31:17.711 --> 00:31:19.796
Okay. well. then there's other missions.

426
00:31:19.880 --> 00:31:21.757
Not if I say no to this one.

427
00:31:21.840 --> 00:31:23.300
Well. she's not up to snuff.

428
00:31:24.843 --> 00:31:27.012
That ship has sailed.

429
00:31:27.095 --> 00:31:30.390
She's on my crew.
and I gotta make it work.

430
00:31:33.477 --> 00:31:35.562
I just gotta make sure
she doesn't screw up.

431
00:31:40.108 --> 00:31:42.528
Maybe I was just meant to fly solo.

432
00:31:44.738 --> 00:31:46.573
Are you trying to hurt my feelings?

433
00:31:48.033 --> 00:31:49.117
I don't mean that.

434
00:31:52.037 --> 00:31:55.249
What happens
if you can't find it within yourself

435
00:31:55.332 --> 00:31:57.209
to play nice with this guy?

436
00:32:01.380 --> 00:32:03.006
I guess he could just bounce me.

437
00:32:05.300 --> 00:32:08.262
What do you think
Patty would think about that?

438
00:32:12.015 --> 00:32:15.519
That I was being an idiot. as usual.

439
00:32:16.311 --> 00:32:21.066
Yeah. Look. I know you know
how to be a part of a team.

440
00:32:24.945 --> 00:32:26.113
Would you...

441
00:32:27.281 --> 00:32:31.076
be up for some team-building exercises?

442
00:32:31.159 --> 00:32:32.703
Well. you seem to be.

443
00:33:12.284 --> 00:33:14.620
-Hello?
-Mornin'. Lar. It's Coop.

444
00:33:14.703 --> 00:33:17.039
So. the training schedule
for the prime crew just shifted up.

445
00:33:17.122 --> 00:33:19.750
and we're gonna need Ellen
in the sim at 0600.

446
00:33:19.833 --> 00:33:20.834
Ellen?

447
00:33:20.918 --> 00:33:23.212
Well. we called her place.
but there was no answer.

448
00:33:23.295 --> 00:33:25.506
So I figured maybe she was with you?

449
00:33:27.758 --> 00:33:31.136
Yeah. Yeah. she's still asleep.

450
00:33:31.970 --> 00:33:35.349
I'll get her there on time. okay?
Just keep this on the QT. will ya?

451
00:33:35.432 --> 00:33:38.560
Don't worry about it.
See you in the sim. you hound dog.

452
00:34:02.543 --> 00:34:05.087
-Hello?
-Pam? It's Larry Wilson.

453
00:34:05.170 --> 00:34:08.005
-Larry? What are you
-Just tell her to get dressed.

454
00:34:08.090 --> 00:34:09.550
I'll be there in 20 minutes.

455
00:34:18.266 --> 00:34:19.768
Who was that?

456
00:34:19.851 --> 00:34:22.938
It's Larry. He'll be here in 20 minutes.

457
00:34:40.706 --> 00:34:45.668
I guess I had one too many
last night at the Outpost.

458
00:34:45.752 --> 00:34:49.547
and Pam just thought it was better
if I didn't drive.

459
00:34:49.630 --> 00:34:52.134
And her house is closer.
spare couch and all. so...

460
00:34:55.387 --> 00:34:56.929
It's not like I was on the clock.
I was just

461
00:34:57.014 --> 00:34:59.057
The two of you are getting sloppy.

462
00:35:03.562 --> 00:35:05.731
I'm not sure I don't know

463
00:35:07.774 --> 00:35:08.942
What are you talking about?

464
00:35:09.026 --> 00:35:10.527
You used to be more careful.

465
00:35:11.987 --> 00:35:13.572
I thought you had your act together.

466
00:35:17.993 --> 00:35:19.369
Have you been spying on me?

467
00:35:19.453 --> 00:35:20.454
You don't have to listen to me.

468
00:35:20.537 --> 00:35:23.248
But if the bosses find out
that you've been lying about anything.

469
00:35:23.707 --> 00:35:24.833
they'll interpret it to mean

470
00:35:24.917 --> 00:35:27.002
that you could lie about something
during a mission.

471
00:35:28.086 --> 00:35:29.963
Like to cover up a mistake.

472
00:35:30.672 --> 00:35:33.050
And from that moment on.
they will put you under the microscope

473
00:35:33.133 --> 00:35:35.427
and they will never. ever let you fly.

474
00:35:35.511 --> 00:35:37.846
-You're overreacting.
-You have to be smarter than this.

475
00:35:38.263 --> 00:35:40.516
Smarter than everyone else.
or you're done.

476
00:35:46.271 --> 00:35:47.731
Believe me. I know.

477
00:35:54.363 --> 00:35:56.114
When we walk into that office.

478
00:35:56.740 --> 00:35:59.284
just act the way they're expecting us to.

479
00:36:03.080 --> 00:36:04.915
If you can pull that off. you'll be fine.

480
00:36:10.963 --> 00:36:11.964
You'll be fine.

481
00:37:13.525 --> 00:37:16.236
All right. everyone.
We're going to the moon. Smile.

482
00:37:18.572 --> 00:37:22.075
Jesus. it's the mopesy twins.
Give us a little more.

483
00:37:22.159 --> 00:37:25.662
You're gonna find ice on the moon
and inspire people all over the world!

484
00:37:27.623 --> 00:37:31.001
Okay. let's get one with just Molly.

485
00:37:31.793 --> 00:37:33.837
Gentlemen. just Molly. please. Thank you.

486
00:37:35.589 --> 00:37:37.716
Molly. could you fluff your hair a bit?

487
00:37:40.010 --> 00:37:43.138
Yeah. that's not working. Can we
get a little help. please? Thank you.

488
00:37:43.222 --> 00:37:45.098
Nixon loves long hair.

489
00:37:45.182 --> 00:37:46.725
That ship has sailed.

490
00:37:46.808 --> 00:37:47.976
Listen. Molly.

491
00:37:48.393 --> 00:37:50.771
Americans wanna see
a free woman on the moon.

492
00:37:50.854 --> 00:37:53.482
Not some Soviet puppet. So. try to smile.

493
00:37:53.565 --> 00:37:57.486
You know. Anastasia's look
beckons us into the cosmos.

494
00:37:57.569 --> 00:37:59.029
You just said she was a puppet.

495
00:37:59.821 --> 00:38:01.532
You need to beckon America.

496
00:38:02.533 --> 00:38:03.784
Askew.

497
00:38:07.246 --> 00:38:08.497
Smile.

498
00:38:11.291 --> 00:38:12.376
Maybe don't smile.

499
00:38:14.503 --> 00:38:15.712
I think we're done.

500
00:40:57.082 --> 00:40:58.584
Well. I'll be a son of a bitch.

501
00:40:58.667 --> 00:41:02.045
Look at you.
Finally. a side of you I like.

502
00:41:02.796 --> 00:41:04.047
You play here a lot?

503
00:41:04.506 --> 00:41:06.842
I don't know. Sometimes.

504
00:41:07.384 --> 00:41:10.179
I guess it helps clear my head
before a launch.

505
00:41:10.804 --> 00:41:12.931
You had a real nice groove going there.

506
00:41:13.599 --> 00:41:15.142
This is my husband. Wayne.

507
00:41:17.144 --> 00:41:18.353
You're married?

508
00:41:18.812 --> 00:41:20.230
It's nice to meet you.

509
00:41:20.314 --> 00:41:21.815
I gotta get the girls down here.

510
00:41:21.899 --> 00:41:23.358
Don't tell anyone.

511
00:41:23.442 --> 00:41:26.612
This is my own time.
It's no one's business but mine.

512
00:41:26.695 --> 00:41:27.696
Whoa. Relax.

513
00:41:27.779 --> 00:41:29.156
I'm serious.

514
00:41:29.239 --> 00:41:31.116
You don't wanna mess with me. Molly.

515
00:41:31.200 --> 00:41:32.743
-Got it?
-I got it.

516
00:41:34.328 --> 00:41:35.537
Nice to meet you. Wayne.

517
00:41:54.598 --> 00:41:57.226
You can't just use your wrist.

518
00:41:58.310 --> 00:42:03.148
In your suit. if you wanna get to the ice.
you need to use your whole arm. okay?

519
00:42:03.232 --> 00:42:04.233
Right.

520
00:42:11.532 --> 00:42:13.617
You can't just pick it up.

521
00:42:14.910 --> 00:42:18.914
You bend in your suit. you can't get
further than 22 inches off the ground.

522
00:42:19.331 --> 00:42:20.874
Let's just leave it for now.

523
00:42:20.958 --> 00:42:23.919
Just focus
on these sample bags. okay?

524
00:42:27.339 --> 00:42:29.508
Get your own bag. They're over there.

525
00:42:29.591 --> 00:42:31.343
Jesus Christ.

526
00:43:02.875 --> 00:43:03.876
Arm down.

527
00:43:11.216 --> 00:43:12.301
This zipper. man.

528
00:43:14.052 --> 00:43:15.721
-You got that?
-Yeah. I got it.

529
00:43:16.346 --> 00:43:19.683
Well. at least
I won't have to wear a bra in space.

530
00:43:20.100 --> 00:43:21.518
Zero-G and all.

531
00:43:21.602 --> 00:43:24.062
Speaking on behalf of Ed and myself.

532
00:43:24.146 --> 00:43:27.065
in the interest
of our respective marriages. please do.

533
00:43:30.027 --> 00:43:31.236
Is there a problem?

534
00:43:31.862 --> 00:43:36.200
Well. we just realized
the relief tube was designed for...

535
00:43:38.160 --> 00:43:39.411
man parts.

536
00:43:40.078 --> 00:43:43.040
She won't be able to use it. I mean.
not without making a hell of a mess.

537
00:43:43.624 --> 00:43:45.876
Let's see. The trip takes. what? A week?

538
00:43:46.418 --> 00:43:48.879
Yeah. I don't think
I can hold it that long.

539
00:43:48.962 --> 00:43:50.255
She could wear a diaper.

540
00:43:50.714 --> 00:43:52.382
Worked for the guys on Gemini.

541
00:43:52.466 --> 00:43:54.301
Molly. Does that sound okay to you?

542
00:43:54.384 --> 00:43:56.970
I'm sorry. Are you kidding? What?

543
00:43:58.347 --> 00:43:59.598
Let me handle this.

544
00:44:00.766 --> 00:44:04.186
No one on my crew is going to the moon
in a damn diaper.

545
00:44:05.062 --> 00:44:08.023
This is NASA.
You're rocket scientists. Figure it out.

546
00:44:09.858 --> 00:44:11.151
It's just a diaper.

547
00:44:12.986 --> 00:44:15.614
So. once you figure out
the controls of the rover...

548
00:44:16.907 --> 00:44:18.492
we'll bring in the 1/6th-g rig

549
00:44:18.575 --> 00:44:20.744
to better simulate its movements
on the moon.

550
00:44:22.204 --> 00:44:25.791
See. the trick is
to keep your eyes on the road.

551
00:44:27.501 --> 00:44:30.671
I'm pretty sure I learned that
in driver's ed... sir.

552
00:44:34.675 --> 00:44:38.136
What I meant is. you're a pilot.

553
00:44:39.221 --> 00:44:40.806
All pilots have tendencies. see?

554
00:44:40.889 --> 00:44:42.266
Every time Gordo drives this thing.

555
00:44:42.349 --> 00:44:45.561
he keeps checking that instrument panel
and then he cross-checks his surrounding.

556
00:44:45.644 --> 00:44:47.813
looking out through the window
like he's in an airplane.

557
00:44:47.896 --> 00:44:48.897
Don't do that.

558
00:44:49.606 --> 00:44:51.650
The terrain's gonna be very irregular.

559
00:44:52.442 --> 00:44:55.320
and even at eight kilometers an hour.
things can happen quick.

560
00:44:56.321 --> 00:44:57.447
Okay?

561
00:44:57.865 --> 00:44:58.866
Got it.

562
00:45:07.040 --> 00:45:09.960
Cobb.
you went into final trim 30 seconds late.

563
00:45:15.841 --> 00:45:18.093
She still doesn't know these procedures.

564
00:45:19.052 --> 00:45:20.846
Let's run it again. Reset.

565
00:45:21.305 --> 00:45:22.556
Roger that.

566
00:45:22.639 --> 00:45:24.224
She is such a pain in my ass.

567
00:45:25.225 --> 00:45:26.852
Resetting to P63.

568
00:45:27.811 --> 00:45:28.854
You know I got this. right?

569
00:45:29.188 --> 00:45:31.815
I was just adjusting
the locking harness out of the way.

570
00:45:31.899 --> 00:45:34.193
And stick to the procedure this time.
Cobb.

571
00:45:34.276 --> 00:45:35.277
Yeah.

572
00:45:49.750 --> 00:45:53.462
Can we... focus. here?

573
00:45:53.545 --> 00:45:57.174
Okay. Noun six two. enter.

574
00:45:57.633 --> 00:46:00.177
Verb two one. enter.

575
00:46:00.260 --> 00:46:02.888
Noun zero one. enter.

576
00:46:03.514 --> 00:46:06.266
Two zero one zero. enter.

577
00:46:06.892 --> 00:46:09.269
Two zero six. enter.

578
00:46:10.938 --> 00:46:13.815
Oh. shit. That was supposed to be
two zero seven. right?

579
00:46:14.608 --> 00:46:15.609
Yep.

580
00:46:15.692 --> 00:46:17.027
All right. let's reset again.

581
00:46:19.738 --> 00:46:21.031
Belay that.

582
00:46:22.032 --> 00:46:24.826
I think we need to rework the procedure
for this stage of the mission.

583
00:46:26.161 --> 00:46:29.164
I'll handle the DSKY entries
until we're in P66.

584
00:46:29.248 --> 00:46:31.875
And I'll actuate the manual throttle
to full on my side.

585
00:46:31.959 --> 00:46:32.960
What? Why?

586
00:46:33.043 --> 00:46:35.712
That's a hell of a change
to be throwing in this late in the game.

587
00:46:35.796 --> 00:46:38.173
Look. Ed. I got this.
I have it under control. I just need

588
00:46:38.257 --> 00:46:42.427
This is my decision. It's final. Copy?

589
00:46:44.346 --> 00:46:45.347
Copy.

590
00:46:45.430 --> 00:46:47.599
Ed. remember why we laid it out that way
in the first place?

591
00:46:47.683 --> 00:46:49.476
I'm the commander of this mission.

592
00:46:49.560 --> 00:46:54.189
If I say to change the procedure. we
change the goddamn procedure. understood?

593
00:46:55.399 --> 00:46:57.776
Now. cut the horseshit out there
and let's get back to work.

594
00:46:59.111 --> 00:47:01.196
Looks like Icy Ed's back in town.

595
00:47:03.866 --> 00:47:05.033
What was that in there?

596
00:47:05.117 --> 00:47:06.952
Fuck off. Margo.
I was just messing with you.

597
00:47:07.035 --> 00:47:11.164
You are too busy joking around in there
to see what's going on.

598
00:47:11.832 --> 00:47:13.250
He doesn't trust you.

599
00:47:13.917 --> 00:47:16.253
-What are you talking about?
-But maybe he shouldn't.

600
00:47:16.670 --> 00:47:20.340
Because the truth is.
you're not good enough. Molly.

601
00:47:21.133 --> 00:47:22.509
Not right now.

602
00:47:22.593 --> 00:47:24.928
And you're gonna be
the first American woman in space.

603
00:47:25.012 --> 00:47:27.431
You have to be perfect.

604
00:47:29.558 --> 00:47:31.018
I am who I am.

605
00:47:31.810 --> 00:47:33.645
If someone doesn't like it.
then screw them.

606
00:47:33.729 --> 00:47:34.980
This isn't just about you.

607
00:47:35.063 --> 00:47:38.150
I'm not trying to be
some goddamn role model for women.

608
00:47:38.233 --> 00:47:39.526
I'm just a pilot!

609
00:47:40.110 --> 00:47:41.195
No.

610
00:47:43.739 --> 00:47:45.407
You're an astronaut.

611
00:48:32.996 --> 00:48:34.248
-Good night.
-You too.

612
00:48:59.898 --> 00:49:01.775
-Keep me safe up there.
-Good luck.

613
00:49:11.159 --> 00:49:12.160
Hey. Ed.

614
00:49:13.537 --> 00:49:14.538
Gordo.

615
00:49:15.289 --> 00:49:16.498
Headed to the Cape.

616
00:49:17.291 --> 00:49:23.213
Yeah. Just one last stop off at home
to say goodbye and... off to Ellington.

617
00:49:24.798 --> 00:49:25.799
Look...

618
00:49:28.427 --> 00:49:32.264
We never got a chance to. you know...

619
00:49:33.640 --> 00:49:35.017
This whole deal. it's just...

620
00:49:35.100 --> 00:49:36.226
Yeah.

621
00:49:36.310 --> 00:49:38.353
Well. I mean. you'll get your... you know?

622
00:49:38.437 --> 00:49:41.773
It's okay. Ed. BOHICA. You know?

623
00:49:44.109 --> 00:49:45.402
BOHICA.

624
00:49:45.485 --> 00:49:46.904
Yeah.

625
00:49:46.987 --> 00:49:50.866
How's Karen feel about you spending a week
in a little capsule with another woman?

626
00:49:52.201 --> 00:49:55.579
I guarantee you she'd be a lot happier
if it was you going up there.

627
00:49:55.662 --> 00:49:56.663
So would I.

628
00:49:56.955 --> 00:50:00.209
Well. changing world.
I hope for the better.

629
00:50:00.626 --> 00:50:01.710
Yep.

630
00:50:02.294 --> 00:50:03.837
Sure it's gonna be a hell of a ride.

631
00:50:07.925 --> 00:50:09.218
Godspeed. 15.

632
00:50:11.428 --> 00:50:14.515
Well. better get back to it.
CAPCOM on the generic sim.

633
00:50:14.598 --> 00:50:17.684
-It's busy work.
-Right. Yeah. Busy. busy.

634
00:50:32.282 --> 00:50:33.367
Look at me.

635
00:50:33.450 --> 00:50:34.576
There you go.

636
00:50:36.828 --> 00:50:37.829
Yes. I see.

637
00:50:38.622 --> 00:50:39.998
You're doing great.

638
00:50:42.876 --> 00:50:44.419
But keep your feet on the pedals.

639
00:50:51.343 --> 00:50:55.556
Attention. all passengers. Bus 163
to San Pedro has been moved to Platform C.

640
00:50:55.639 --> 00:50:57.891
Here. This should last the whole trip.

641
00:50:58.600 --> 00:51:02.771
Okay. Aleida. This is the first ticket.
Now. where do you get off the bus?

642
00:51:02.855 --> 00:51:06.358
Cape Kennedy. It's the last stop tomorrow
morning. and I don't get off before then.

643
00:51:06.441 --> 00:51:09.236
Okay. And what happens
when you get to Cape Kennedy?

644
00:51:09.319 --> 00:51:12.406
I follow the people there because
they'll all be going to the same place.

645
00:51:12.906 --> 00:51:16.952
When it's over. I walk to the bus station
and use the second ticket

646
00:51:17.035 --> 00:51:18.745
Papa. I need the second ticket.

647
00:51:21.123 --> 00:51:22.207
Sorry.

648
00:51:22.958 --> 00:51:26.461
And the second ticket takes me back home
to Houston. Which is also the last stop.

649
00:51:26.545 --> 00:51:28.630
And you don't get off the bus before then.

650
00:51:28.714 --> 00:51:29.840
-I know.
-Okay.

651
00:51:31.675 --> 00:51:35.596
Aleida. I'm sorry
I didn't have enough for two tickets.

652
00:51:35.679 --> 00:51:37.890
I'll be okay. Papa. I promise.

653
00:51:37.973 --> 00:51:39.183
Okay.

654
00:51:42.102 --> 00:51:43.103
I love you.

655
00:51:45.147 --> 00:51:46.773
I'll be right here when you get back.

656
00:51:47.941 --> 00:51:49.109
Sorry.

657
00:52:16.178 --> 00:52:18.680
-Hello?
-Where the hell were you last night?

658
00:52:19.723 --> 00:52:22.476
I unplugged my phone
to get a good night's sleep. What's wrong?

659
00:52:22.893 --> 00:52:25.229
Nothing. I just... I don't know.

660
00:52:27.314 --> 00:52:29.942
What if there'd been an emergency
with one of the boys?

661
00:52:30.025 --> 00:52:31.527
Well. did something happen. babe?

662
00:52:31.610 --> 00:52:34.404
No. but what if it did?

663
00:52:34.488 --> 00:52:36.698
You know Baseops can get to me anytime.

664
00:52:37.157 --> 00:52:38.408
Yeah. I guess.

665
00:52:41.578 --> 00:52:42.788
So. when are you coming back?

666
00:52:44.540 --> 00:52:46.416
I don't know. A few days. maybe.

667
00:52:46.500 --> 00:52:48.877
You're going out tonight to celebrate?

668
00:52:49.461 --> 00:52:52.631
Well. I don't know. Maybe.
You know what it's like here.

669
00:52:53.048 --> 00:52:54.842
What's that supposed to mean?

670
00:52:54.925 --> 00:52:56.468
Well. I mean...

671
00:52:57.177 --> 00:52:59.930
-I don't know. It's launch day. you know?
-Yep.

672
00:53:01.223 --> 00:53:04.935
Yeah. okay. I just thought
you were worried about being a bad mother.

673
00:53:13.986 --> 00:53:14.987
What was that?

674
00:53:15.946 --> 00:53:16.947
What was what. hon?

675
00:53:18.615 --> 00:53:20.284
Hey. I gotta run.

676
00:53:20.367 --> 00:53:22.578
-I'll call you later. Love you.
-Hey. wai

677
00:54:11.627 --> 00:54:14.630
I don't understand. I mean.
we were a few rows up for Apollo 10.

678
00:54:14.713 --> 00:54:16.757
It seems okay to me. We're closer. anyway.

679
00:54:18.091 --> 00:54:20.093
I just liked it better
where we sat before.

680
00:54:21.094 --> 00:54:22.262
Hi. ladies.

681
00:54:22.763 --> 00:54:24.056
Hello. Excuse me.

682
00:54:28.644 --> 00:54:29.645
Is that him?

683
00:54:30.145 --> 00:54:31.146
That's him.

684
00:54:36.652 --> 00:54:37.694
-Hello.
-Yeah.

685
00:54:37.778 --> 00:54:39.571
-Karen Baldwin.
-Wayne Cobb.

686
00:54:41.615 --> 00:54:42.824
That's a great dress.

687
00:54:43.992 --> 00:54:45.160
-Thank you.
-Yeah.

688
00:55:28.954 --> 00:55:29.872
Tighter.

689
00:55:31.456 --> 00:55:32.457
Tighter.

690
00:57:28.490 --> 00:57:30.909
That was quite a send-off.

691
00:57:33.704 --> 00:57:35.789
Buncha people cheering for shit.

692
00:57:36.373 --> 00:57:37.875
I haven't done anything yet.

693
00:57:39.877 --> 00:57:43.797
You did just strap your ass on top of
a quarter million tons of high explosive

694
00:57:43.881 --> 00:57:45.299
for government pay.

695
00:57:46.425 --> 00:57:49.469
It's not smart. but it's something.

696
00:57:59.188 --> 00:58:00.981
Final guidance alignment.

697
00:58:01.064 --> 00:58:04.067
The final maneuver
the astronauts perform before liftoff.

698
00:58:07.654 --> 00:58:10.574
Twenty-five seconds and counting.
We are still go.

699
00:58:11.950 --> 00:58:16.038
Twenty seconds. Guidance alert.
The guidance system now going internal.

700
00:58:16.747 --> 00:58:21.168
Fifteen. 14. 13. 12. 11.

701
00:58:21.251 --> 00:58:26.298
ten. nine. eight. ignition sequence start.

702
00:58:26.798 --> 00:58:32.262
five. four. three. two. one. zero.

703
00:58:33.472 --> 00:58:36.725
Launch commit. Liftoff. We have liftoff.

704
00:58:42.648 --> 00:58:44.399
The tower is clear.

705
00:59:18.559 --> 00:59:20.394
Hey. Deke. You got a call.

706
00:59:23.272 --> 00:59:25.482
Hey. We did it. huh?

707
00:59:25.566 --> 00:59:27.609
Terrific. right? Come on in.

708
00:59:35.826 --> 00:59:36.827
Slayton.

709
00:59:36.910 --> 00:59:39.913
This is the White House operator.
Please hold for the president.

710
00:59:40.998 --> 00:59:45.502
I like what I'm seeing on the news. Deke.
Quite a show. Congratulations.
